<br>
In order to not trivialize encounters with manaburn, you change how it works to the following.<br>
<br>
NPC's Level 60 and lower are immune to Manaburn<br>
<br>
Don't mess with PvP, that's their style of play. <br>
However by doing this, they lose a lot of their farmed mobs. This does include gore, talendor, severilous, venril sathir, and a few other burnable mobs.<br>
<br>
Would this be wrong? Heck no. This would restrict it to raid use only against NPCs, the way it SHOULD be, to give them an edge, but not an overpowering advantage against a 250-500k hp mob.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, the class skill's  original perpose was to be used for higher end raids, not 60 and lower mobs. <br>
<br>
Can wizards whine? Yep, and they will, but they will simply show themselves as the farmers when they do so. <br>
Any respectable wizard would keep this ability put away until they were hitting up some Ssra or NToV mob. <br>
<br>
What does this fix?<br>
Warrior epic<br>
Bard epic<br>
Paladin epic<br>
Mid-tier guild raids<br>
Farming issues<br>
Complaints to VI<br>
Class specific legs(kunark)<br>
<br>
As far as Severilous is concerned, he can be 1-grouped now with ease, no need for level 65 and PoP gear lol.<br>
60 warrior(4500+ unbuffed HP)<br>
60 cleric<br>
60 enchanter<br>
60 shaman<br>
60 rogue<br>
60 bard<br>
<br>
Logged out:Necro for DMF<br>
<br>
The fight itself is over before it begins if you have proper resists. How hard is it for a 6500+ hp tank to take a beating from a mob hitting 300-500, slowed and crippled.<br>
<br>
That's basicly the fight nowadays. Not much harder than the very first snakes in Ssra who hit for 270's. <br>
<br>
<br>
Shaman keeps Severilous slowed and chain-banes for 2kish dmg in 45 seconds each.<br>
<br>
Warrior hits quad 80ish, with sometimes a tripple attack. Hasted with VoG+decent haste item, they can put out a few thousand before the first bane wears off.<br>
<br>
Rogue hits quad 80-100, backstabbing for 300-500's. <br>
<br>
